# Documentation Standards

## Documentation Structure
The project includes comprehensive documentation:

- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Main project overview
- [docs/](mdc:docs/) - Detailed documentation
- [IMPROVEMENT_COMPLETION_REPORT.md](mdc:IMPROVEMENT_COMPLETION_REPORT.md) - Recent improvements
- [REFACTORING_SUMMARY.md](mdc:REFACTORING_SUMMARY.md) - Refactoring details

## Markdown Standards

### Formatting Rules
- **Lists**: Always surround lists with blank lines (MD032 compliance)
- **Headers**: Use consistent header hierarchy
- **Code Blocks**: Use appropriate language tags for syntax highlighting
- **Links**: Use relative paths for internal documentation links

### List Formatting (MD032 Compliance)
```markdown
### Section Header

- List item 1
- List item 2

More content after the list.
```

### Code Examples
```markdown
```zig
const std = @import("std");
const database = @import("database");

pub fn main() !void {
    var db = try database.Db.open("vectors.wdbx", true);
    defer db.close();
}
```
```

