## Documentation Best Practices
- Use clear, concise language
- Include code examples for complex concepts
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes
- Use consistent formatting throughout
- Include troubleshooting sections where appropriate

## Markdown Linting
- Ensure MD032 compliance (blank lines around lists)
- Use consistent heading levels
- Include alt text for images
- Use descriptive link text
- Maintain consistent formatting

## Documentation Updates
- Update documentation when making API changes
- Include examples for new features
- Update version information when releasing
- Keep migration guides current
- Document breaking changes clearly